flowRoot.flowPara: Julia is a relatively new programming language designed for technical computing. It is designed to be simple and expressive, but perform at speeds comparable to C. It has a substantial package library and an elegant foreign function interface, with which one can easily call C, R, and Python.

text.tspan: The Julia language: a fresh approach

flowRoot.flowPara: This four-hour workshop will be by taught by Jeff Bezanson, co-creator of Julia, and will introduce the language, going from basics through data handling and parallelism.
Workshop for FH employees: 9am-2pm Weds February 15.
